  <h2 class="hide-text">Search Results</h2>

  <div id="documents">
  <div class="document blacklight-archival-collection">
  <div class="documentHeader clearfix">
  
    <h5 class="index_title">1. <i class="contenttypes-archival_collection"></i><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/findingaids/html/fales/bloch/" target="_blank">Guide to the Mark Bloch Postal Art Network (PAN) Archive (MSS 170)</a></h5>

  
  <div class="documentFunctions col-md-2"></div>
</div>



  

  <dl class="dl-horizontal dl-invert">

	      <dt class="blacklight-repository_ssi">Library:</dt>
	      <dd class="blacklight-repository_ssi"><a href="/fales">The Fales Library &amp; Special Collections</a></dd>
	      <dt class="blacklight-title_ssm">Title:</dt>
	      <dd class="blacklight-title_ssm">Mark Bloch Postal Art Network (PAN) Archive</dd>
	      <dt class="blacklight-abstract_ssm">Abstract:</dt>
	      <dd class="blacklight-abstract_ssm">Mark Bloch is an American fine artist and writer whose work utilizes both visuals and text to explore ideas of long distance communication. This collection contains thousands of examples of original “mail art” sent to and collected by Mark Bloch in New York City from all fifty states and dozens of countries in the form of objects, envelopes, artwork, and enclosures as well as publications, postcards and announcements documenting avant garde cultural activities in various media during the years 1978 to 2013.</dd>
	      <dt class="blacklight-format_ssm">Format:</dt>
	      <dd class="blacklight-format_ssm">Archival Collection</dd>
	      <dt class="blacklight-language_ssm">Language:</dt>
	      <dd class="blacklight-language_ssm">English</dd>
	      <dt class="blacklight-unitdate_ssm">Dates:</dt>
	      <dd class="blacklight-unitdate_ssm">Inclusive, 1978-2012</dd>
	      <dt class="blacklight-collection_ssm">Archival Collection:</dt>
	      <dd class="blacklight-collection_ssm"><a href="/catalog?f%5Bcollection_sim%5D%5B%5D=Mark+Bloch+Postal+Art+Network+%28PAN%29+Archive&amp;f%5Bformat_sim%5D%5B%5D=Archival+Collection&amp;q=World+War+II&amp;search_field=The+Fales+Library+%26+Special+Collections">Mark Bloch Postal Art Network (PAN) Archive</a></dd>
  <dt>Table of Contents:</dt>
    <dd><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/findingaids/html/fales/bloch/" target="_blank">Descriptive Summary</a></dd>
    <dd><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/findingaids/html/fales/bloch/bioghist.html" target="_blank">Historical/Biographical Note</a></dd>
    <dd><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/findingaids/html/fales/bloch/scopecontent.html" target="_blank">Scope and Content Note and Arrangement</a></dd>
    <dd><a href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/findingaids/html/fales/bloch/controlaccess.html" target="_blank">Access Points</a></dd>
    
  <dt>Archival Items:</dt>
    <dd><b><a href="/catalog?f%5Bcollection_sim%5D%5B%5D=Mark+Bloch+Postal+Art+Network+%28PAN%29+Archive&amp;q=World+War+II&amp;search_field=The+Fales+Library+%26+Special+Collections&amp;sort=series_si+asc%2C+box_filing_si+asc">Click here to search within collection</a></b></dd>


